{
  "style": "",
  "texts": [
    "A dictionary can be represented by a directed graph, with each word a vertex, and an edge from each defining (content) word to the (content) words it defines.",
    "(Content-words are words that have referents -nouns, verbs and adjectives.)",
    "The question \"What is the smallest number of (content) words from which all the other (content) words can be defined?\"",
    "is equivalent to the problem of finding the minimum feedback vertex set of the directed dictionary graph.",
    "That smallest number is surprisingly small -of the order of about 1000 words."
  ],
  "correct_citations": []
}